{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SNd1pVfeYdeV6a35u8p3qn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: 0.6.0 Acceptance Criteria\n3\tdate: 2026-04-27\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Testable AC-NNN criteria; each maps to a REQ + test id\n6\tblast_radius: test-plan.md (every AC → ≥1 test); requirements.md (every REQ → ≥1 AC); CI gate definitions; release-checklist.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Acceptance Criteria\n11\t\n12\tFormat:\n13\t\n14\t```markdown\n15\t## AC-NNN: <short title>\n16\t\n17\t**Requirement ref:** REQ-NNN\n18\t**Test id:** T-NNN (placeholder; bound by test-plan.md)\n19\t**Assertion:** <single observable, measurable, falsifiable statement>\n20\t**Measurement:** <how it's checked>\n21\t**Fixture:** <name of fixture, or \"test-plan.md fixture spec — pending\">\n22\t```\n23\t\n24\tRules:\n25\t\n26\t- Unique `AC-NNN` id; numbering stable; suffixes a/b/c when an outcome\n27\t  splits.\n28\t- One assertion per AC (no compounds — no AND chains, no comma-list of\n29\t  observables).\n30\t- No \"should / ideally / reasonable\" — binary outcomes only.\n31\t- Every REQ in `requirements.md` has ≥1 AC.\n32\t- Every AC has a placeholder T-NNN; `test-plan.md` (Phase 3f) binds\n33\t  T-NNN to real test scaffolds.\n34\t- Every AC names its fixture, or explicitly marks the fixture as\n35\t  pending `test-plan.md`. ACs whose fixture is pending are\n36\t  **lock-blocking** on `test-plan.md`.\n37\t- Numerical gates restate the cited accepted ADR. AC must not\n38\t  introduce numbers absent from the ADR — if a measurement parameter\n39\t  (warmup, sample count, tolerance) is needed beyond the ADR, the\n40\t  parameter is owned by `test-plan.md`, not invented inline.\n41\t\n42\tT-NNN ids are placeholders until `test-plan.md` issues real ones.\n43\t\n44\t## Parameter table\n45\t\n46\tacceptance.md OWNS every numerical measurement parameter cited by an\n47\tAC. test-plan.md is the _measurer_ — it executes the protocol but does\n48\tnot own the threshold. Parameters with an ADR source restate the ADR.\n49\tParameters without an ADR source are owned by this doc and bound at\n50\tacceptance lock; changing them post-lock follows the same critic + HITL"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4cda15f5-dd21-46d9-b4db-04d61e252748","uuid":"028bdfcc-789a-4cd9-a240-fce0280b9ce2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T22:17:29.938Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-11c-set-version-20260516T221655Z/dev/acceptance.md","content":"---\ntitle: 0.6.0 Acceptance Criteria\ndate: 2026-04-27\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Testable AC-NNN criteria; each maps to a REQ + test id\nblast_radius: test-plan.md (every AC → ≥1 test); requirements.md (every REQ → ≥1 AC); CI gate definitions; release-checklist.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\n\nFormat:\n\n```markdown\n## AC-NNN: <short title>\n\n**Requirement ref:** REQ-NNN\n**Test id:** T-NNN (placeholder; bound by test-plan.md)\n**Assertion:** <single observable, measurable, falsifiable statement>\n**Measurement:** <how it's checked>\n**Fixture:** <name of fixture, or \"test-plan.md fixture spec — pending\">\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- Unique `AC-NNN` id; numbering stable; suffixes a/b/c when an outcome\n  splits.\n- One assertion per AC (no compounds — no AND chains, no comma-list of\n  observables).\n- No \"should / ideally / reasonable\" — binary outcomes only.\n- Every REQ in `requirements.md` has ≥1 AC.\n- Every AC has a placeholder T-NNN; `test-plan.md` (Phase 3f) binds\n  T-NNN to real test scaffolds.\n- Every AC names its fixture, or explicitly marks the fixture as\n  pending `test-plan.md`. ACs whose fixture is pending are\n  **lock-blocking** on `test-plan.md`.\n- Numerical gates restate the cited accepted ADR. AC must not\n  introduce numbers absent from the ADR — if a measurement parameter\n  (warmup, sample count, tolerance) is needed beyond the ADR, the\n  parameter is owned by `test-plan.md`, not invented inline.\n\nT-NNN ids are placeholders until `test-plan.md` issues real ones.\n\n## Parameter table\n\nacceptance.md OWNS every numerical measurement parameter cited by an\nAC. test-plan.md is the _measurer_ — it executes the protocol but does\nnot own the threshold. Parameters with an ADR source restate the ADR.\nParameters without an ADR source are owned by this doc and bound at\nacceptance lock; changing them post-lock follows the same critic + HITL","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1190}}}
