{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkPABrorhoynE8JnseqBeF","type":"tool_result","content":"60\t  - Repath `python/` -> `src/python/`, `typescript/` -> `src/ts/`.\n61\t  - Drop the `cargo build -p fathomdb --features node` step until napi-rs\n62\t    lands.\n63\t  - Re-target `python-stress-tests` to whatever `--features python` /\n64\t    binding shape Phase 11 chose.\n65\t\n66\t## scripts/set-version.sh — Phase 11\n67\t\n68\t- Source: `git show 39ee271^:scripts/set-version.sh`\n69\t- Why deferred (resolved 2026-05-12): release-process policy is now\n70\t  resolved in `dev/design/release.md`. Rewrite `set-version.sh` to enforce\n71\t  the two version axes (Axis W lockstep across workspace + bindings; Axis\n72\t  E independent for `fathomdb-embedder-api`).\n73\t- Pre-push hook (`scripts/hooks/pre-push`) intentionally does not call\n74\t  `set-version.sh --check-files` for 0.6.0 — the script does not exist in\n75\t  this tree. Restore the pre-push step in the same PR that restores the\n76\t  script.\n77\t\n78\t## What stayed minimal on day one\n79\t\n80\t`.github/workflows/ci.yml` collapses three pre-0.6.0 workflows\n81\t(`ci.yml`, `python.yml`, `typescript.yml`) into a single\n82\t`bootstrap -> agent-verify` job plus a\n83\tmulti-OS rust matrix and a `docs` job, because `scripts/agent-verify.sh`\n84\talready fans out lint -> typecheck -> test across Rust/Python/TS/markdown\n85\t(see AGENTS.md §3). Splitting the workflow back out only buys parallelism;\n86\tdefer that until CI wall time becomes a problem.\n87\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4cda15f5-dd21-46d9-b4db-04d61e252748","uuid":"2a2f6b85-b1be-4833-a62d-ec24ba40b71a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T22:17:36.129Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-11c-set-version-20260516T221655Z/dev/plans/ci-deferred.md","content":"  - Repath `python/` -> `src/python/`, `typescript/` -> `src/ts/`.\n  - Drop the `cargo build -p fathomdb --features node` step until napi-rs\n    lands.\n  - Re-target `python-stress-tests` to whatever `--features python` /\n    binding shape Phase 11 chose.\n\n## scripts/set-version.sh — Phase 11\n\n- Source: `git show 39ee271^:scripts/set-version.sh`\n- Why deferred (resolved 2026-05-12): release-process policy is now\n  resolved in `dev/design/release.md`. Rewrite `set-version.sh` to enforce\n  the two version axes (Axis W lockstep across workspace + bindings; Axis\n  E independent for `fathomdb-embedder-api`).\n- Pre-push hook (`scripts/hooks/pre-push`) intentionally does not call\n  `set-version.sh --check-files` for 0.6.0 — the script does not exist in\n  this tree. Restore the pre-push step in the same PR that restores the\n  script.\n\n## What stayed minimal on day one\n\n`.github/workflows/ci.yml` collapses three pre-0.6.0 workflows\n(`ci.yml`, `python.yml`, `typescript.yml`) into a single\n`bootstrap -> agent-verify` job plus a\nmulti-OS rust matrix and a `docs` job, because `scripts/agent-verify.sh`\nalready fans out lint -> typecheck -> test across Rust/Python/TS/markdown\n(see AGENTS.md §3). Splitting the workflow back out only buys parallelism;\ndefer that until CI wall time becomes a problem.\n","numLines":28,"startLine":60,"totalLines":87}}}
